Import or export data to a PostgreSQL database, scripts must be run from this
directory.

Environment variables used by scripts:

  SQLITE3: sqlite3 command to use

./import.sh <database> [<typeschema>] <schema> [drop]

Import SCOWL data into PostgreSQL.  <database> is the PostgreSQL database.
<schema> is the schema to import the data into; if the schema doesn't exist it
will be created; if 'drop' is specified then the schema will be recreated if
it exists; otherwise, all tables are truncated.  <typeschema> specifies the
schema for enum types; if the schema doesn't exists it will be created and
populated.

The env. var. SCOWL_DB can be used to set the sqlite3 db file, otherwise it
defaults to '../scowl.db'

./export.sh <database> <schema> <sqlite-db-file>

Export SCOWL data from PostgreSQL.

